//           "1. Manage Stress Well\n\nPeople today are overworked and overwhelmed. But, in the end it must be remembered that drugs only make life more stressful. The way to avoid drugs in this case is to find something else to manage stress. Choose positive activities that help take your mind off stress-relieving drugs.\n\n\n2. Avoid Drinking Alcohol\n\nDrinking and drug abuse often go hand in hand. Those with mental health illnesses may turn to drugs and alcohol for solutions. Because of this, avoid drinking alcohol which can have adverse effects on health.\n\n\n3. More Exercise \n\nThe way to avoid drugs and alcohol can be by exercising regularly every day. When you exercise, it will increase endorphins, dopamine, adrenaline, and endocannabinoids. this is a series of chemicals in the brain that can trigger feelings of happiness, confidence, and reduce anxiety and stress.",
